cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.SC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper uses algebraic geometry to study matrix rigidity. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of computing a matrix-vector product. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the degrees of varieties associated to rigidity. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses families of matrices that are expected to have super-linear rigidity. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is relevant as the paper discusses ideals and degrees of cones.
